  "text": "Rollins et al. suggest reducing postoperative blood loss through use of small intravenous cannulae, avoidance of unnecessary intravenous lines, and wound drainage to reinfuse drained content [CITATION_1] . Such procedures seem at least controversial and not exactly effective, for which reason they are not sanctioned in our department.",
